Defendant Victor J Puente in court with attorney Eryn M Menden.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Previously stayed capias is quashed. Attorney Menden states that the Defendant did not complete Drug Treatment Court. Defendant previously pled guilty on count 1 for Deferred Prosecution. Deferred Prosecution is revoked. Court will find the Defendant guilty of count #1. State gives sentencing recommendations. Attorney Menden makes sentencing recommendation. Defendant makes statements.The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

3 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 17 days)
  -  1.5 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  1.5 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISON 

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS	***TRANSFER ALLOWED TO RACINE COUNTY***

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
____AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol, illegal drugs, or drug paraphernalia;
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
prescribed.
____Inform Agent of all prescriptions, sign releases
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with: victim listed in the criminal complaint or their residence. 
____DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done

RESTITUTION:  $43.23 (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines)

FINE or COSTS:  $278.00 + $250.00  (to be paid as a condition of probation)

CONDITION TIME: 90 days-Non-working hours with standard release conditions, STAYED for use of agent with court permission. 

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program. 

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
